# Gotime Settings Module - Project Intelligence

## Project Patterns

### File Naming
- Components: PascalCase (`HolidaysTab.tsx`)
- Hooks: camelCase with `use` prefix (`useHolidays.ts`)
- Services: camelCase with `Service` suffix (`holidaysService.ts`)
- Types: grouped in `gotime.types.ts`

### Ant Design Usage
- Always use `theme.useToken()` for styling values
- Use `App.useApp()` for feedback (message, modal, notification)
- Prefer `Flex` over native div for layouts
- Use `Typography.Text`/`Paragraph` instead of span/p

### Service Pattern
```typescript
export const EntityService = {
  list: async (params): Promise<Entity[]> => {...},
  create: async (data): Promise<Entity> => {...},
  update: async (id, data): Promise<Entity> => {...},
  delete: async (id): Promise<void> => {...}
};
```

### Hook Pattern
- Always return `{ data, loading, error, handlers }`
- Use services for all data operations
- Provide callbacks for CRUD actions

